metadata.name: BAI #98
metadata.description:
The first blueprint was found in 1947 on the northwestern shore of the Dead Sea.
It has been studied several times.
Numerous theories arose trying to explain its origin.
None of them was decided conclusively.

One year ago, a rare group of waves coming from space was intercepted on earth.
This happened during the 2021 summer.
It was unclear if they were born from natural events.
Dying stars, black holes... Humans tried to find patterns. Find a meaning for them.
None of the analyses made any sense.

Bai was a young physicist and Ph.D. student.
Her mother was a civil engineer working in finance.
Her father was an architect and a generative artist.
She had a personal interest in linguistics and algorithmic art, influenced by her father.
She was the one who managed to decrypt the information using her own algorithms.

Those frequencies were the gate to sets of technical drawings, matching precisely the physical blueprint found in 1947.

It's been a year since the waves were discovered.
No definite conclusions have been made yet regarding their origin or their meaning.
Nevertheless, the number of theories keeps increasing with every new blueprint decrypted.

The frequencies keep passing by the earth.
There is still so much investigation to be carried out.
So many questions to be answered.
Yet, the financial crisis is making the budget for investigation decrease rapidly.
The Institute of Space Sciences is running an initiative to self-fund this project.
Three hundred thirteen open spots can then seize those waves.
Encapsulating them as NFTs.


—--------------------

This project is an attempt to experiment with two main ideas arising from technical plans:

1. The inner beauty of architectural plans, city plans, industrial blueprints, and any other type of documents of that nature. A study of graphic elements like annotations, dashed lines, grids, etc. disposed of in different manners to create aesthetically appealing compositions.

2. How does the viewer analyze and interpret abstract compositions of technical plans? Triggering different thoughts and ideas: A Rorschach test with blueprints instead of ink blots.

—--------------------

All the minters at the first tear of the dutch auction will be able to claim A or B: A being one HD signed print of their blueprint or B their unique 1/1, on top of the NFT minted.

Those unique 1/1s will be pre-curated outputs from this algorithm. Some of the 1/1 parameters could be chosen by the minter: colors, main composition, shapes, density, name of the blueprint... so that the result will be a collaboration between the minter, Ismahelio, and the algorithm itself.

Minters at the second tier of the dutch auction can claim one unique 1/1. The difference with the first tier is that the minter won't be involved in the design process. The piece will be designed and curated by Ismahelio.

If there are any of these 1/1s to be claimed. They will be minted within an Objkt.com collection and airdropped to the minters.

—--------------------
Heavily dense compositions might not load on some mobile devices with insufficient memory.
The quality of the piece on phones and tablets has been decreased programmatically.
Visualize the piece in a powerful enough computer for the best experience.

Click 1: Activate
Click 2: increase speed
1: save 4000x4000 png
2: save 6000x6000 png
3: save 8000x8000 png

Original piece by Ismahelio.
August 2022. Madrid - Cadiz. Spain.
Made with p5.js

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #138
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Shape Study  #109
metadata.description:
“Everyone has their own shape.”
We meet shapes of all kinds in our life.

Algorithmic randomness generates shapes ever so slightly different yet similar. 
I suppose these are someone’s collection.

“Why do they need to have so many similar things?”

Perhaps it’s their versatility in the pleasure they could bring.
Perhaps they’re meant for different occasions.
Perhaps some are left to search for their very own shapes.

Seeing this, I realized that when people explore themselves or others, it is also a form of shape study.
With what’s visible and concrete, explore the unseen and abstract.

However, good shapes only come by chance.
Shapes, in truth, cannot be good or bad in and of themselves. It’s only when two shapes come together that the meaning thereof arises.
I hope you who decide to pick up this work will find the shapes to your liking.

『每個人都有自己的形狀』
並且每個人一生中也會認識各種形狀

程式的隨機性讓我產生的每個形狀都相似而不同
我想像這也許是某個人的蒐藏
『為什麼會需要擁有這麼多相似的道具呢？』

也許是它們有著不同的功能，能帶來不同的愉悅；
也許是適用於不同的場景
也許是遲遲未找到屬於自己的形狀

想像至此，我意識到：當人們探索自己／他人的同時，也可以說是一種形狀研究
用一個看得見的具體，去探索一個看不見的抽象

然而，好的形狀是可遇不可求的
其實形狀本身沒有好壞，只有當兩個形狀相遇時，形狀才有了意義
希望蒐藏這件作品的各位都可以遇到喜歡的形狀

metadata.name: Kings of Babylon #152
metadata.description:
Excavate Kings from the past.
Some are born first, and some are born later.
The long-dead are no longer breathless.
The new kings hail from distant dimensions.
Hunt their crowns, peel their eyes and savor in their glory.

25 Backgrounds
7 Forms
8 Mouths
26 Crowns
12 Eyes

Every Friday for 6 weeks, 2 Kings will be animated and airdropped to the holder, chosen through raffle ritual.
Check @syamarahakim and @spirouzi for the ritual.

metadata.name: Sleepless #57
metadata.description:
Sleepless is a generative art project made from p5.js. Inspired by the artist's travels, the project emulates a window view of a distant city at night. Variations include randomization of different window elements (frames and bars) and city elements (buildings, planes and ships). It is also mintable in several foreground and background colors. The colors and dithering were selected to create a charcoal texture.

Press 'S' to download a high res PNG.
Due to the preview image being compressed to fit your window size, the dithering may look different from the high res PNG.

NFTs minted are under the NFT License 2.0 (https://www.nftlicense.org/)

metadata.name: White Night Vol.1 #87
metadata.description:
I have a long-term photography project called “White Night”, which explores special images of trees through black and white inversion.

I attempt to generate similar images by code, and this is the start of the journey.

Made with p5js.

Controls:
- Press “f” to toggle the frame, there is my signature on the mat inside the frame.
- Press “s” to save the image displayed at that moment as a PNG file.
- Change the canvas size by adding “size” URL parameter, for example: &size=1000 (you may add this and lower the number if your device can’t render properly)
